---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import { YouTube } from "astro-embed";
---

<MainLayout title="About Us">
    <section class="overflow-hidden">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 sm:py-20">
            <div
                class="mx-auto grid max-w-2xl grid-cols-1 gap-x-8 gap-y-16 sm:gap-y-20 lg:mx-0 lg:max-w-none lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-start"
            >
                <div class="lg:max-w-lg prose">
                    <h1
                        class="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-6xl uppercase"
                    >
                        About Us
                    </h1>

                    <p class="text-lg font-medium text-pretty sm:text-xl/7">
                        We are proud to have become a full member league of the
                        Women’s Flat Track Derby Association in March of 2014,
                        which means that we joined the ranks of 470 women-led,
                        skater owned and operated leagues worldwide that have
                        united to lead the sport of women’s flat track roller
                        derby.
                    </p>

                    <figure class="mt-12">
                        <blockquote class="text-base/7">
                            <p>
                                An inspiring quote from a team member saying how
                                awesome derby is and how proud they are to be
                                part of the team.
                            </p>
                        </blockquote>
                        <figcaption class="mt-6 flex gap-x-4 text-sm/6">
                            <img
                                src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1509783236416-c9ad59bae472?ixlib=rb-=eyJhcHBfaWQiOjEyMDd9&auto=format&fit=facearea&facepad=8&w=1024&h=1024&q=80"
                                alt=""
                                class="size-6 flex-none rounded-full mt-0 mb-0"
                            />
                            <div>
                                <span class="font-semibold">Jane Doe</span> – Team
                                Member or something
                            </div>
                        </figcaption>
                    </figure>

                    <h2>WFTDA</h2>
                    <p>
                        The Women’s Flat Track Derby Association is the
                        international governing body for the sport of women’s
                        flat track roller derby and a membership organization
                        for leagues to collaborate and network. The WFTDA sets
                        standards for <a
                            target="_blank"
                            href="https://wftda.org/rules">rules</a
                        >, seasons, and safety, and determines guidelines for
                        the national and international athletic competitions of
                        member leagues.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <img
                    src="https://dht7q8fif4gks.cloudfront.net/2025-11/572095564_18408401341142527_7253166904574926156_n.jpg"
                    alt="Roller Derby Team Photo"
                    class="w-[48rem] max-w-none rounded-xl ring-1 shadow-xl ring-gray-400/10 sm:w-[57rem] md:-ml-4 lg:ml-0"
                    width="2432"
                    height="1442"
                />
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 lg:px-8 pb-24 sm:pb-32 prose">
        <div
            class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-12 gap-y-16 lg:grid-cols-6 items-start"
        >
            <div class="lg:col-span-2">
                <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl lg:mx-0">
                    <h2
                        class="text-3xl uppercase tracking-tight text-pretty text-white sm:text-4xl"
                    >
                        Community Outreach
                    </h2>
                </div>
                <p>
                    The Renegade Derby Dames have been involved in community
                    outreach since the founding of the league, providing
                    fundraising support and donations to local charities. Over
                    the years, we have contributed to the Royal LePage Shelter
                    Foundation for women’s shelters and violence prevention, and
                    we donated a Derby Girl For A Day package for the David
                    Busby Centre Silent Auction to benefit the homeless. With
                    50/50 draws at our bouts, we have helped My Sisters Place
                    raise money to support their work helping women and their
                    children who have been victims of violence in the home.
                </p><p>
                    We have participated in the Trick-or-Eat Campaign, gathering
                    over 1,000 pounds of non-perishable food items for the Good
                    Shepherd Food Bank in recent years, in addition to the food
                    donations that we accept at every bout. In 2013, we hosted a
                    charity EradiSKATE Cancer tournament, raising over $2300 for
                    Matthew’s House Hospice in Alliston.
                </p>
            </div>

            <aside class="lg:col-span-4 top-8">
                <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl lg:mx-0">
                    <h2
                        class="text-3xl uppercase tracking-tight text-pretty text-white sm:text-4xl"
                    >
                        What is Flat Track Roller Derby?
                    </h2>
                </div>
                <p>
                    Flat track roller derby is a fast-paced contact team sport
                    that requires speed, strategy, and athleticism. The flat
                    track version of the sport evolved in 2001, and has quickly
                    grown to encompass more than 400 leagues worldwide. This is
                    due in large part to the ease of setting up a flat track–it
                    can be done on any flat surface that is suitable for
                    skating, such as skating rinks, basketball courts, parking
                    lots, and even airplane hangars. This greatly reduces the
                    capital needed to start up a roller derby league.
                </p>
                <YouTube id="OId6gTd2LCM" />
            </aside>
        </div>
    </section>
</MainLayout>
